  "text": "Various poly(amidoamine) (PAMAM) dendrimers were applied to the selectively nucleate, the most unstable polymorph of CaCO 3 , vaterite. Vaterite is preferred from a technological perspective as it exhibits higher solubility, higher surface area, and higher dispersability. The generation or size of the PAMAM dendrimers controlled the particle size and size distribution of the resultant vaterite [CITATION_1] . We predict that drug crystal polymorphism will soon be templated by nanoconfinement in dendrimer crystallization platforms.",
